Document: MenuBar
Path: godot/classes/class_menubar.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties available for configuring a MenuBar node, including its appearance, language settings, global menu integration, and behavior.

Properties:
*   flat (bool): Flat MenuBar don't display item decoration. Default: false.
    Method: set_flat(value: bool)
    Method: is_flat()
*   language (String): Language code used for line-breaking and text shaping algorithms. If left empty, the current locale is used instead. Default: "".
    Method: set_language(value: String)
    Method: get_language()
*   prefer_global_menu (bool): If true, MenuBar will use system global menu when supported. Default: true.
    Note: If true and global menu is supported, this node is not displayed, has zero size, and all its child nodes except PopupMenus are inaccessible.
    Note: This property overrides the value of the PopupMenu.prefer_native_menu property of the child nodes.
    Method: set_prefer_global_menu(value: bool)
    Method: is_prefer_global_menu()
*   start_index (int): Position order in the global menu to insert MenuBar items at. All menu items in the MenuBar are always inserted as a continuous range. Menus with lower start_index are inserted first. Menus with start_index equal to -1 are inserted last. Default: -1.
    Method: set_start_index(value: int)
    Method: get_start_index()
*   switch_on_hover (bool): If true, when the cursor hovers above menu item, it will close the current PopupMenu and open the other one. Default: true.
    Method: set_switch_on_hover(value: bool)
    Method: is_switch_on_hover()
*   text_direction (TextDirection): Base text writing direction. Default: 0.
    Method: set_text_direction(value: TextDirection)
    Method: get_text_direction()
---CHUNK---
Document: MenuBar
Path: godot/classes/class_menubar.rst
Summary: This section describes methods for querying and manipulating menu items within a MenuBar.

Method: get_menu_count() → int
Returns number of menu items.

Method: get_menu_popup(menu: int) → PopupMenu
Returns PopupMenu associated with menu item.

Method: get_menu_title(menu: int) → String
Returns menu item title.

Method: get_menu_tooltip(menu: int) → String
Returns menu item tooltip.

Method: is_menu_disabled(menu: int) → bool
Returns true if the menu item is disabled.

Method: is_menu_hidden(menu: int) → bool
Returns true if the menu item is hidden.

Method: is_native_menu() → bool
Returns true if the current system's global menu is supported and used by this MenuBar.

Method: set_disable_shortcuts(disabled: bool) → void
If true, shortcuts are disabled and cannot be used to trigger the button.

Method: set_menu_disabled(menu: int, disabled: bool) → void
If true, menu item is disabled.

Method: set_menu_hidden(menu: int, hidden: bool) → void
If true, menu item is hidden.

Method: set_menu_title(menu: int, title: String) → void
Sets menu item title.

Method: set_menu_tooltip(menu: int, tooltip: String) → void
Sets menu item tooltip.
