Document: MenuBar
Path: godot/classes/class_menubar.rst
Summary: This section details the theme properties available for customizing the appearance and behavior of MenuBar items, including colors, fonts, sizes, and styleboxes for various states.

Theme Property Descriptions:
*   font_color (Color): Default text Color of the menu item. Default: Color(0.875, 0.875, 0.875, 1).
*   font_disabled_color (Color): Text Color used when the menu item is disabled. Default: Color(0.875, 0.875, 0.875, 0.5).
*   font_focus_color (Color): Text Color used when the menu item is focused. Only replaces the normal text color of the menu item. Disabled, hovered, and pressed states take precedence over this color. Default: Color(0.95, 0.95, 0.95, 1).
*   font_hover_color (Color): Text Color used when the menu item is being hovered. Default: Color(0.95, 0.95, 0.95, 1).
*   font_hover_pressed_color (Color): Text Color used when the menu item is being hovered and pressed. Default: Color(1, 1, 1, 1).
*   font_outline_color (Color): The tint of text outline of the menu item. Default: Color(0, 0, 0, 1).
*   font_pressed_color (Color): Text Color used when the menu item is being pressed. Default: Color(1, 1, 1, 1).
*   h_separation (int): The horizontal space between menu items. Default: 4.
*   outline_size (int): The size of the text outline. Default: 0. Note: If using a font with FontFile.multichannel_signed_distance_field enabled, its FontFile.msdf_pixel_range must be set to at least twice the value of outline_size for outline rendering to look correct. Otherwise, the outline may appear to be cut off earlier than intended.
*   font (Font): Font of the menu item's text.
*   font_size (int): Font size of the menu item's text.
*   disabled (StyleBox): StyleBox used when the menu item is disabled.
*   disabled_mirrored (StyleBox): StyleBox used when the menu item is disabled (for right-to-left layouts).
*   hover (StyleBox): StyleBox used when the menu item is being hovered.
*   hover_mirrored (StyleBox): StyleBox used when the menu item is being hovered (for right-to-left layouts).
*   hover_pressed (StyleBox): StyleBox used when the menu item is being pressed and hovered at the same time.
*   hover_pressed_mirrored (StyleBox): StyleBox used when the menu item is being pressed and hovered at the same time (for right-to-left layouts).
*   normal (StyleBox): Default StyleBox for the menu item.
*   normal_mirrored (StyleBox): Default StyleBox for the menu item (for right-to-left layouts).
*   pressed (StyleBox): StyleBox used when the menu item is being pressed.
*   pressed_mirrored (StyleBox): StyleBox used when the menu item is being pressed (for right-to-left layouts).